summary:
- **Delisting Announcement**:  
  - GDC (Global Data Centre Group) has applied for voluntary removal from the ASX (Listing Rule 17.11).  
  - **Reason**: Completion of asset disposals (last asset sold Dec 2024) and distribution of proceeds ($1.44/unit in May 2025). Group now holds only cash; winding up entities post-delisting.  
  - **Key Condition**: Delisting will occur **27 June 2025**, after capital return completion.  
  - **Consequences**: Units will no longer trade on ASX; residual cash may be returned during wind-up (FY26–FY32).  
  - **Timetable**:  
    - 27 Jun 2025: Expected delisting date.  

*No other material trading/capital markets information identified.*
